import os import json import time from ddgs import DDGS print("=== PIANIST WITH 25-YEAR HIATUS AND FAUR√â CONNECTION - FIXED VARIABLE SCOPING ===\n") print("Objective: Find a pianist who took a 25-year hiatus and was first to perform complete Faur√© piano works\n") # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') print("Created workspace directory\n") # Define search queries search_queries = [ "pianist 25 year hiatus Faur√© complete piano works", "first complete Faur√© piano works concert performance", "classical pianist retirement comeback Faur√© Gabriel", "Faur√© complete piano cycle first performer history" ] print(f"Conducting {len(search_queries)} searches...\n") # Initialize searcher searcher = DDGS(timeout=10) # Store all raw results without processing all_raw_results = [] search_errors = [] for query_index, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): print(f"--- Search {query_index}/{len(search_queries)}: {query} ---") try: results = searcher.text( query, max_results=4, page=1, backend=["duckduckgo"], safesearch="off", region="en-us" ) if results and len(results) > 0: print(f"Found {len(results)} results") for result_index, result in enumerate(results, 1): # Extract basic data safely - NO PROCESSING YET title = result.get('title', 'No title') snippet = result.get('body', result.get('snippet', 'No snippet')) url = result.get('href', result.get('url', 'No URL')) print(f" Result {result_index}: {title[:80]}...") # Store raw result raw_result = { 'query': query, 'query_index': query_index, 'result_index': result_index, 'title': title, 'snippet': snippet, 'url': url } all_raw_results.append(raw_result) else: print("No results returned") except Exception as e: error_msg = f"Search {query_index} failed: {str(e)}" print(error_msg) search_errors.append(error_msg) time.sleep(2) print() # Save raw results immediately raw_data = { 'objective': 'Find pianist with 25-year hiatus who first performed complete Faur√© piano works', 'timestamp': '2024-12-19', 'total_queries': len(search_queries), 'successful_results': len(all_raw_results), 'search_errors': search_errors, 'raw_results': all_raw_results } with open('workspace/pianist_faure_raw_results.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(raw_data, f, indent=2) print(f"=== RAW RESULTS SAVED ===\n") print(f"Total raw results collected: {len(all_raw_results)}") print(f"Search errors: {len(search_errors)}") print(f"Raw data saved to: workspace/pianist_faure_raw_results.json\n") # Now process the raw results with proper variable scoping print("=== PROCESSING RAW RESULTS WITH FIXED SCOPING ===\n") processed_results = [] relevant_results = [] processing_errors = [] for i, raw_result in enumerate(all_raw_results, 1): print(f"Processing result {i}/{len(all_raw_results)}") try: # Extract data from raw result title = raw_result['title'] snippet = raw_result['snippet'] url = raw_result['url'] query = raw_result['query'] print(f" Title: {title[:60]}...") # CRITICAL FIX: Define combined_text OUTSIDE any conditional logic combined_text = f"{title} {snippet}".lower() # Now perform analysis with properly scoped variable has_pianist = any(term in combined_text for term in ['pianist', 'piano', 'performer', 'musician', 'artist']) has_hiatus = any(term in combined_text for term in ['hiatus', 'retirement', 'comeback', 'return', 'break', 'absence', 'years']) has_faure = any(term in combined_text for term in ['faur√©', 'faure', 'gabriel']) has_complete = any(term in combined_text for term in ['complete', 'entire', 'all', 'full', 'cycle', 'works']) # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = sum([has_pianist, has_hiatus, has_faure, has_complete]) # Create processed result processed_result = { 'title': title, 'snippet': snippet, 'url': url, 'query': query, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'has_pianist': has_pianist, 'has_hiatus': has_hiatus, 'has_faure': has_faure, 'has_complete': has_complete } processed_results.append(processed_result) # Show relevance factors factors = [] if has_pianist: factors.append('Pianist') if has_hiatus: factors.append('Hiatus') if has_faure: factors.append('Faur√©') if has_complete: factors.append('Complete Works') print(f" Relevance Score: {relevance_score}/4 ({', '.join(factors) if factors else 'No key factors'})") # Add to relevant if score >= 2 if relevance_score >= 2: relevant_results.append(processed_result) print(f" ‚úì Added to relevant results") print() except Exception as e: error_msg = f"Error processing result {i}: {str(e)}" print(f" {error_msg}") processing_errors.append(error_msg) continue print(f"=== PROCESSING COMPLETE ===\n") print(f"Successfully processed: {len(processed_results)} results") print(f"Relevant results (score >= 2): {len(relevant_results)}") print(f"Processing errors: {len(processing_errors)}") if processing_errors: print(f"\nProcessing errors:") for error in processing_errors: print(f" - {error}") if relevant_results: print(f"\n=== TOP RELEVANT RESULTS ===\n") # Sort by relevance score sorted_relevant = sorted(relevant_results, key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) for i, result in enumerate(sorted_relevant, 1): print(f"--- Relevant Result {i} (Score: {result['relevance_score']}/4) ---") print(f"Title: {result['title']}") print(f"URL: {result['url']}") print(f"Query: {result['query']}") print(f"Snippet: {result['snippet'][:200]}..." if len(result['snippet']) > 200 else f"Snippet: {result['snippet']}") # Show context text_lower = all_text.lower() term_pos = text_lower.find(term.lower()) if term_pos != -1: context_start = max(0, term_pos - 60) context_end = min(len(all_text), term_pos + len(term) + 60) context = all_text[context_start:context_end] print(f" Context: ...{context}...") print() # Now perform analysis with properly scoped variable has_pianist = any(term in combined_text for term in ['pianist', 'piano', 'performer', 'musician', 'artist']) has_hiatus = any(term in combined_text for term in ['hiatus', 'retirement', 'comeback', 'return', 'break', 'absence', 'years']) has_faure = any(term in combined_text for term in ['faur√©', 'faure', 'gabriel']) has_complete = any(term in combined_text for term in ['complete', 'entire', 'all', 'full', 'cycle', 'works']) # Add to relevant if score >= 2 if relevance_score >= 2: relevant_results.append(processed_result) print(f" ‚úì Added to relevant results") print() except Exception as e: error_msg = f"Error processing result {i}: {str(e)}" print(f" {error_msg}") processing_errors.append(error_msg) continue print(f"=== PROCESSING COMPLETE ===\n") print(f"Successfully processed: {len(processed_results)} results") print(f"Relevant results (score >= 2): {len(relevant_results)}") print(f"Processing errors: {len(processing_errors)}") if processing_errors: print(f"\nProcessing errors:") for error in processing_errors: print(f" - {error}") if relevant_results: print(f"\n=== TOP RELEVANT RESULTS ===\n") # Look for the raw results file that was successfully created raw_results_file = None for file in workspace_files: if 'pianist' in file.lower() and 'raw' in file.lower() and file.endswith('.json'): raw_results_file = file break if raw_results_file: print(f"\n=== ANALYZING RAW RESULTS FILE: {raw_results_file} ===\n") # First inspect the structure with open(f'workspace/{raw_results_file}', 'r') as f: raw_data = json.load(f) print("File structure:") for key, value in raw_data.items(): if isinstance(value, list): print(f" {key}: List with {len(value)} items") elif isinstance(value, dict): print(f" {key}: Dictionary with {len(value)} keys") else: print(f" {key}: {value}") # Extract and analyze the raw results if 'raw_results' in raw_data: raw_results = raw_data['raw_results'] print(f"\n=== PROCESSING {len(raw_results)} RAW SEARCH RESULTS ===\n") # Process each result manually without the problematic variable scoping relevant_results = [] pianist_names = set() faure_sources = [] for i, result in enumerate(raw_results, 1): title = result.get('title', 'No title') snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet') url = result.get('url', 'No URL') query = result.get('query', 'No query') print(f"--- Result {i} ---") print(f"Title: {title}") print(f"URL: {url}") print(f"Query: {query}") print(f"Snippet: {snippet[:150]}..." if len(snippet) > 150 else f"Snippet: {snippet}") # Manual relevance analysis without problematic variable text_to_analyze = f"{title} {snippet}".lower() # Check for key terms has_pianist = any(term in text_to_analyze for term in ['pianist', 'piano', 'performer', 'musician', 'artist']) has_hiatus = any(term in text_to_analyze for term in ['hiatus', 'retirement', 'comeback', 'return', 'break', 'absence', 'years']) has_faure = any(term in text_to_analyze for term in ['faur√©', 'faure', 'gabriel']) has_complete = any(term in text_to_analyze for term in ['complete', 'entire', 'all', 'full', 'cycle', 'works']) relevance_score = sum([has_pianist, has_hiatus, has_faure, has_complete]) # Show analysis factors = [] if has_pianist: factors.append('Pianist') if has_hiatus: factors.append('Hiatus') if has_faure: factors.append('Faur√©') if has_complete: factors.append('Complete Works') print(f"Relevance Score: {relevance_score}/4 ({', '.join(factors) if factors else 'No key factors'})") # Extract potential names from title and snippet import re name_pattern = r'\b[A-Z][a-z]{2,}\s+[A-Z][a-z]{2,}\b' found_names = re.findall(name_pattern, f"{title} {snippet}") # Filter out common non-names exclude_terms = { 'Gabriel Faur√©', 'New York', 'Los Angeles', 'United States', 'Great Britain', 'Piano Music', 'Complete Works', 'Classical Music', 'Concert Hall', 'Classic FM', 'Sony Classical', 'Music Web', 'Piano World', 'Red Balloon', 'Century Rec', 'Higher Hz', 'Chamber Music', 'Lincoln Center', 'Bru Zane' } filtered_names = [name for name in found_names if name not in exclude_terms] if filtered_names: print(f"Potential Names: {', '.join(filtered_names)}") pianist_names.update(filtered_names) # Check for specific promising content if 'thyssens-valentin' in text_to_analyze: print("*** PROMISING LEAD: Germaine Thyssens-Valentin mentioned ***") if 'debargue' in text_to_analyze: print("*** PROMISING LEAD: Lucas Debargue mentioned ***") if 'first' in text_to_analyze and 'complete' in text_to_analyze: print("*** PROMISING: Contains 'first' and 'complete' references ***") # Add to relevant results if score >= 2 if relevance_score >= 2: relevant_results.append({ 'title': title, 'snippet': snippet, 'url': url, 'query': query, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'factors': factors, 'names_found': filtered_names }) print("‚úì Added to relevant results") # Collect Faur√©-related sources if has_faure: faure_sources.append({ 'title': title, 'url': url, 'relevance_score': relevance_score }) print() print(f"=== ANALYSIS SUMMARY ===\n") print(f"Total results analyzed: {len(raw_results)}") print(f"Relevant results (score >= 2): {len(relevant_results)}") print(f"Faur√©-related sources: {len(faure_sources)}") print(f"Potential pianist names found: {len(pianist_names)}") if pianist_names: print(f"\nPotential pianist names:") for name in sorted(pianist_names): print(f" - {name}") if relevant_results: print(f"\n=== TOP RELEVANT RESULTS ===\n") # Sort by relevance score sorted_relevant = sorted(relevant_results, key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) for i, result in enumerate(sorted_relevant[:5], 1): print(f"--- Top Result {i} (Score: {result['relevance_score']}/4) ---") print(f"Title: {result['title']}") print(f"URL: {result['url']}") print(f"Factors: {', '.join(result['factors'])}") if result['names_found']: print(f"Names: {', '.join(result['names_found'])}") print(f"Snippet: {result['snippet'][:200]}..." if len(result['snippet']) > 200 else f"Snippet: {result['snippet']}") print() # Look for specific clues about 25-year hiatus print(f"=== SEARCHING FOR 25-YEAR HIATUS CLUES ===\n") all_text = ' '.join([r['title'] + ' ' + r['snippet'] for r in raw_results]) hiatus_terms = ['25 year', 'twenty-five year', 'hiatus', 'retirement', 'comeback', 'return'] for term in hiatus_terms: count = all_text.lower().count(term.lower()) if count > 0: print(f"'{term}': Found {count} times") # Show context text_lower = all_text.lower() term_pos = text_lower.find(term.lower()) if term_pos != -1: context_start = max(0, term_pos - 80) context_end = min(len(all_text), term_pos + len(term) + 80) context = all_text[context_start:context_end] print(f" Context: ...{context}...") print() # Save processed analysis final_analysis = { 'objective': 'Find pianist with 25-year hiatus who first performed complete Faur√© piano works', 'data_recovery_successful': True, 'total_raw_results': len(raw_results), 'relevant_results_count': len(relevant_results), 'faure_sources_count': len(faure_sources), 'potential_pianist_names': list(pianist_names), 'top_relevant_results': sorted_relevant[:5] if relevant_results else [], 'faure_sources': faure_sources, 'key_findings': [ 'Found multiple Faur√©-related Wikipedia pages', 'Identified potential pianist names in search results', 'Located sources about complete Faur√© piano works', 'Need to investigate specific pianist names further' ], 'next_steps': [ 'Search specifically for each potential pianist name found', 'Investigate Wikipedia "Piano music of Gabriel Faur√©" page', 'Look up Germaine Thyssens-Valentin and Lucas Debargue', 'Search for "25-year hiatus" with classical pianist names', 'Check French language sources for Faur√© performance history' ] } with open('workspace/pianist_faure_recovered_analysis.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(final_analysis, f, indent=2) print(f"Recovered analysis saved to: workspace/pianist_faure_recovered_analysis.json") # import os import json print("=== PIANIST WITH 25-YEAR HIATUS AND FAUR√â CONNECTION - SIMPLE DATA EXTRACTION ===\n") print("Objective: Extract and analyze the raw search data using basic Python operations\n") # First, let's inspect what files we have in workspace print("=== WORKSPACE INSPECTION ===\n") if os.path.exists('workspace'): workspace_files = os.listdir('workspace') print(f"Files in workspace: {len(workspace_files)}") for file in sorted(workspace_files): file_path = os.path.join('workspace', file) if os.path.isfile(file_path): file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path) print(f" - {file} ({file_size:,} bytes)") else: print("No workspace directory found") exit() # Look for the raw results file raw_results_file = None for file in workspace_files: if 'pianist' in file.lower() and 'raw' in file.lower() and file.endswith('.json'): raw_results_file = file break if raw_results_file: print(f"\n=== LOADING RAW RESULTS FILE: {raw_results_file} ===\n") # Load and inspect the file structure first with open(f'workspace/{raw_results_file}', 'r') as f: raw_data = json.load(f) print("File structure:") for key, value in raw_data.items(): if isinstance(value, list): print(f" {key}: List with {len(value)} items") elif isinstance(value, dict): print(f" {key}: Dictionary with {len(value)} keys") else: print(f" {key}: {value}") # Process each result with simple, safe operations for i, result in enumerate(raw_results, 1): print(f"--- Result {i} ---") # Extract basic information safely title = result.get('title', 'No title') snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet') url = result.get('url', 'No URL') query = result.get('query', 'No query') print(f"Title: {title}") print(f"URL: {url}") print(f"Query: {query}") print(f"Snippet: {snippet[:150]}..." if len(snippet) > 150 else f"Snippet: {snippet}") # Create combined text for analysis - SIMPLE ASSIGNMENT combined_content = title + " " + snippet lower_content = combined_content.lower() # Check for key terms using simple operations pianist_terms = ['pianist', 'piano', 'performer', 'musician', 'artist'] hiatus_terms = ['hiatus', 'retirement', 'comeback', 'return', 'break', 'absence', 'years'] faure_terms = ['faur√©', 'faure', 'gabriel'] complete_terms = ['complete', 'entire', 'all', 'full', 'cycle', 'works'] # Count matches pianist_match = False hiatus_match = False faure_match = False complete_match = False for term in pianist_terms: if term in lower_content: pianist_match = True break for term in hiatus_terms: if term in lower_content: hiatus_match = True break for term in faure_terms: if term in lower_content: faure_match = True break for term in complete_terms: if term in lower_content: complete_match = True break # Calculate relevance score score = 0 if pianist_match: score += 1 if hiatus_match: score += 1 if faure_match: score += 1 if complete_match: score += 1 # Show analysis factors = [] if pianist_match: factors.append('Pianist') if hiatus_match: factors.append('Hiatus') if faure_match: factors.append('Faur√©') if complete_match: factors.append('Complete Works') print(f"Relevance Score: {score}/4 ({', '.join(factors) if factors else 'No key factors'})") # Extract potential names using simple regex import re name_pattern = r'\b[A-Z][a-z]{2,}\s+[A-Z][a-z]{2,}\b' found_names = re.findall(name_pattern, combined_content) # Filter out obvious non-names exclude_list = [ 'Gabriel Faur√©', 'New York', 'Los Angeles', 'United States', 'Great Britain', 'Piano Music', 'Complete Works', 'Classical Music', 'Concert Hall', 'Classic FM', 'Sony Classical', 'Music Web', 'Piano World', 'Red Balloon', 'Century Rec', 'Higher Hz', 'Chamber Music', 'Lincoln Center', 'Bru Zane', 'Roman Polanski', 'Adrien Brody', 'Ronald Harwood' ] filtered_names = [] for name in found_names: if name not in exclude_list: filtered_names.append(name) if filtered_names: print(f"Potential Names: {', '.join(filtered_names)}") all_pianist_names.extend(filtered_names) # Check for specific promising content if 'thyssens' in lower_content or 'valentin' in lower_content: print("*** PROMISING LEAD: Thyssens-Valentin mentioned ***") if 'debargue' in lower_content: print("*** PROMISING LEAD: Debargue mentioned ***") if '25' in combined_content and 'year' in lower_content: print("*** PROMISING: Contains 25-year reference ***") hiatus_mentions.append(combined_content) # Collect relevant results if score >= 2: relevant_results.append({ 'title': title, 'snippet': snippet, 'url': url, 'query': query, 'score': score, 'factors': factors, 'names': filtered_names }) print("‚úì Added to relevant results") # Collect Faur√©-related sources if faure_match: faure_related.append({ 'title': title, 'url': url, 'score': score }) print() # Remove duplicate names unique_names = list(set(all_pianist_names)) print(f"=== ANALYSIS SUMMARY ===\n") print(f"Total results analyzed: {len(raw_results)}") print(f"Relevant results (score >= 2): {len(relevant_results)}") print(f"Faur√©-related sources: {len(faure_related)}") print(f"Unique potential pianist names: {len(unique_names)}") print(f"25-year hiatus mentions: {len(hiatus_mentions)}") if unique_names: print(f"\nPotential pianist names found:") for name in sorted(unique_names): print(f" - {name}") if hiatus_mentions: print(f"\n25-year references found:") for mention in hiatus_mentions: print(f" - {mention[:100]}...") if relevant_results: print(f"\n=== TOP RELEVANT RESULTS ===\n") # import os import json import time from ddgs import DDGS print("=== TARGETED SEARCH FOR PIANIST WITH 25-YEAR HIATUS - FOLLOW-UP INVESTIGATION ===\n") print("Objective: Conduct targeted searches based on previous findings to identify the specific pianist\n") # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') print("Created workspace directory\n") # First, let's check what we learned from previous searches print("=== REVIEWING PREVIOUS FINDINGS ===\n") # Look for existing analysis files existing_files = [] if os.path.exists('workspace'): for file in os.listdir('workspace'): if 'pianist' in file.lower() and file.endswith('.json'): existing_files.append(file) print(f"Found previous analysis: {file}") # Load previous findings if available previous_names = [] if existing_files: for file in existing_files: try: with open(f'workspace/{file}', 'r') as f: data = json.load(f) # Extract any pianist names mentioned if 'unique_pianist_names' in data: previous_names.extend(data['unique_pianist_names']) elif 'potential_pianist_names' in data: previous_names.extend(data['potential_pianist_names']) except Exception as e: print(f"Could not load {file}: {str(e)}") # Remove duplicates and filter relevant names filtered_names = [] for name in set(previous_names): # Filter out obvious non-pianist names if not any(term in name.lower() for term in ['wikipedia', 'classical clips', 'grand piano', 'records', 'the pianist']): if len(name.split()) == 2: # Likely a real person name filtered_names.append(name) print(f"\nFiltered pianist names from previous searches: {len(filtered_names)}") for name in sorted(filtered_names): print(f" - {name}") # Define new targeted search queries targeted_queries = [ "\"25 year hiatus\" pianist classical music comeback", "pianist retirement 25 years return Faur√©", "\"first complete Faur√© piano works\" concert history", "Germaine Thyssens-Valentin complete Faur√© piano works", "Lucas Debargue Faur√© complete piano cycle", "Laurent Wagschal Faur√© piano complete recordings" ] # Add searches for specific names found previously for name in filtered_names[:3]: # Limit to top 3 to avoid too many searches targeted_queries.append(f'\"{name}\" 25 year hiatus pianist') targeted_queries.append(f'\"{name}\" Faur√© complete piano works') print(f"\n=== CONDUCTING {len(targeted_queries)} TARGETED SEARCHES ===\n") # Initialize searcher searcher = DDGS(timeout=10) # Store all results targeted_results = [] search_errors = [] for query_index, query in enumerate(targeted_queries, 1): print(f"--- Targeted Search {query_index}/{len(targeted_queries)}: {query} ---") try: results = searcher.text( query, max_results=3, # Fewer results per query since we have more queries page=1, backend=["duckduckgo"], safesearch="off", region="en-us" ) if results and len(results) > 0: print(f"Found {len(results)} results") for result_index, result in enumerate(results, 1): title = result.get('title', 'No title') snippet = result.get('body', result.get('snippet', 'No snippet')) url = result.get('href', result.get('url', 'No URL')) print(f" Result {result_index}: {title[:60]}...") # Store result targeted_result = { 'query': query, 'query_index': query_index, 'result_index': result_index, 'title': title, 'snippet': snippet, 'url': url } targeted_results.append(targeted_result) else: print("No results returned") except Exception as e: error_msg = f"Targeted search {query_index} failed: {str(e)}" print(error_msg) search_errors.append(error_msg) time.sleep(1.5) # Shorter delay since we have more searches print() print(f"=== TARGETED SEARCH COMPLETE ===\n") print(f"Total targeted results collected: {len(targeted_results)}") print(f"Search errors: {len(search_errors)}") # Save raw targeted results targeted_data = { 'objective': 'Find specific pianist with 25-year hiatus who first performed complete Faur√© piano works', 'search_type': 'targeted_follow_up', 'timestamp': '2024-12-19', 'total_queries': len(targeted_queries), 'successful_results': len(targeted_results), 'search_errors': search_errors, 'targeted_results': targeted_results } with open('workspace/pianist_faure_targeted_results.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(targeted_data, f, indent=2) print(f"Targeted results saved to: workspace/pianist_faure_targeted_results.json\n") # Process the targeted results immediately with simple operations print("=== PROCESSING TARGETED RESULTS ===\n") highly_relevant = [] specific_leads = [] all_names_found = [] for i, result in enumerate(targeted_results, 1): title = result['title'] snippet = result['snippet'] url = result['url'] query = result['query'] # Create combined text for analysis combined_text = f"{title} {snippet}".lower() print(f"--- Processing Targeted Result {i} ---") print(f"Title: {title}") print(f"Query: {query}") print(f"URL: {url}") print(f"Snippet: {snippet[:150]}..." if len(snippet) > 150 else f"Snippet: {snippet}") # Check for key indicators has_hiatus = any(term in combined_text for term in ['hiatus', 'retirement', 'comeback', 'return', 'break', 'absence']) has_25_years = '25' in combined_text and 'year' in combined_text has_faure = any(term in combined_text for term in ['faur√©', 'faure', 'gabriel']) has_complete = any(term in combined_text for term in ['complete', 'entire', 'all', 'full', 'cycle']) has_first = 'first' in combined_text has_pianist = any(term in combined_text for term in ['pianist', 'piano', 'performer']) # Calculate specificity score specificity_score = sum([has_hiatus, has_25_years, has_faure, has_complete, has_first, has_pianist]) # Show analysis factors = [] if has_hiatus: factors.append('Hiatus') if has_25_years: factors.append('25-Years') if has_faure: factors.append('Faur√©') if has_complete: factors.append('Complete') if has_first: factors.append('First') if has_pianist: factors.append('Pianist') print(f"Specificity Score: {specificity_score}/6 ({', '.join(factors) if factors else 'No key factors'})") # Extract names import re name_pattern = r'\b[A-Z][a-z]{2,}\s+[A-Z][a-z]{2,}\b' found_names = re.findall(name_pattern, f"{title} {snippet}") # Filter names exclude_terms = { 'Gabriel Faur√©', 'New York', 'Los Angeles', 'United States', 'Great Britain', 'Piano Music', 'Complete Works', 'Classical Music', 'Concert Hall', 'Classic FM', 'Sony Classical', 'Music Web', 'Piano World', 'Red Balloon', 'Century Rec', 'Higher Hz', 'Chamber Music', 'Lincoln Center', 'Bru Zane', 'Roman Polanski', 'Adrien Brody', 'Ronald Harwood', 'Victor Hugo', 'Apple Music', 'Amazon Music' } filtered_names = [name for name in found_names if name not in exclude_terms] if filtered_names: print(f"Names Found: {', '.join(filtered_names)}") all_names_found.extend(filtered_names) # Check for specific promising indicators if has_25_years and has_hiatus: print("*** HIGHLY PROMISING: Contains both 25-year and hiatus references ***") specific_leads.append({ 'title': title, 'snippet': snippet, 'url': url, 'query': query, 'reason': '25-year hiatus mentioned' }) if 'thyssens' in combined_text or 'valentin' in combined_text: print("*** SPECIFIC LEAD: Thyssens-Valentin mentioned ***") specific_leads.append({ 'title': title, 'snippet': snippet, 'url': url, 'query': query, 'reason': 'Thyssens-Valentin mentioned' }) if has_first and has_complete and has_faure: print("*** PROMISING: First complete Faur√© performance mentioned ***") # Add to highly relevant if score >= 4 if specificity_score >= 4: highly_relevant.append({ 'title': title, 'snippet': snippet, 'url': url, 'query': query, 'specificity_score': specificity_score, 'factors': factors, 'names_found': filtered_names }) print("‚úì Added to highly relevant results") print() # Remove duplicate names unique_names = list(set(all_names_found)) print(f"=== TARGETED SEARCH ANALYSIS SUMMARY ===\n") print(f"Total targeted results processed: {len(targeted_results)}") print(f"Highly relevant results (score >= 4): {len(highly_relevant)}") print(f"Specific leads identified: {len(specific_leads)}") print(f"Unique names found: {len(unique_names)}") if unique_names: print(f"\nNew pianist names discovered:") for name in sorted(unique_names): print(f" - {name}") if specific_leads: print(f"\n=== SPECIFIC LEADS TO INVESTIGATE ===\n") for i, lead in enumerate(specific_leads, 1): print(f"--- Lead {i}: {lead['reason']} ---") print(f"Title: {lead['title']}") print(f"URL: {lead['url']}") print(f"Query: {lead['query']}") print(f"Snippet: {lead['snippet'][:200]}..." if len(lead['snippet']) > 200 else f"Snippet: {lead['snippet']}") print() if highly_relevant: print(f"=== HIGHLY RELEVANT RESULTS ===\n") sorted_relevant = sorted(highly_relevant, key=lambda x: x['specificity_score'], reverse=True) for i, result in enumerate(sorted_relevant, 1): print(f"--- Highly Relevant {i} (Score: {result['specificity_score']}/6) ---") print(f"Title: {result['title']}") print(f"URL: {result['url']}") print(f"Factors: {', '.join(result['factors'])}") if result['names_found']: print(f"Names: {', '.join(result['names_found'])}") print(f"Snippet: {result['snippet'][:200]}..." if len(result['snippet']) > 200 else f"Snippet: {result['snippet']}") print() # Save comprehensive targeted analysis final_targeted_analysis = { 'objective': 'Find specific pianist with 25-year hiatus who first performed complete Faur√© piano works', 'search_phase': 'targeted_follow_up', 'analysis_completed': True, 'total_targeted_results': len(targeted_results), 'highly_relevant_count': len(highly_relevant), 'specific_leads_count': len(specific_leads), 'unique_names_found': unique_names, 'specific_leads': specific_leads, 'highly_relevant_results': sorted_relevant if highly_relevant else [], 'key_findings': [ f'Conducted {len(targeted_queries)} targeted searches', f'Found {len(specific_leads)} specific leads to investigate', f'Identified {len(unique_names)} new potential pianist names', f'Located {len(highly_relevant)} highly relevant sources' ], 'immediate_next_steps': [ 'Investigate any specific leads found', 'Research each unique pianist name individually', 'Focus on Thyssens-Valentin if mentioned in results', 'Check academic sources for Faur√© performance history', 'Search French language sources if needed' ] } with open('workspace/pianist_faure_targeted_analysis.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(final_targeted_analysis, f, indent=2) print(f"Targeted analysis saved to: workspace/pianist_faure_targeted_analysis.json") # Create final summary final_summary = { 'search_status': 'Targeted follow-up searches completed', 'total_searches_conducted': len(targeted_queries), 'key_discoveries': { 'specific_leads': len(specific_leads), 'highly_relevant_results': len(highly_relevant), 'new_pianist_names': unique_names }, 'most_promising_leads': [lead['title'] for lead in specific_leads[:3]], 'next_phase': 'Individual investigation of specific leads and names' } with open('workspace/pianist_search_final_summary.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(final_summary, f, indent=2) print(f"Final summary saved to: workspace/pianist_search_final_summary.json") print(f"\n=== TARGETED SEARCH INVESTIGATION COMPLETE ===\n") print("Successfully conducted targeted follow-up searches based on previous findings.") print(f"\nKey achievements:") print(f"‚úì Conducted {len(targeted_queries)} targeted searches") print(f"‚úì Found {len(specific_leads)} specific leads requiring investigation") print(f"‚úì Identified {len(highly_relevant)} highly relevant results") print(f"‚úì Discovered {len(unique_names)} new potential pianist names") print(f"‚úì Created comprehensive analysis for next phase of investigation") print(f"\nFiles created:") for file in os.listdir('workspace'): if 'targeted' in file.lower() or 'final' in file.lower(): if file.endswith('.json'): file_size = os.path.getsize(f'workspace/{file}') print(f" - {file} ({file_size:,} bytes)")

import os import json import time from ddgs import DDGS print("=== TARGETED SEARCH FOR PIANIST WITH 25-YEAR HIATUS - FOLLOW-UP INVESTIGATION ===\n") print("Objective: Conduct targeted searches based on previous findings to identify the specific pianist\n") # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') print("Created workspace directory\n") # First, let's check what we learned from previous searches print("=== REVIEWING PREVIOUS FINDINGS ===\n") # Look for existing analysis files existing_files = [] if os.path.exists('workspace'): for file in os.listdir('workspace'): if 'pianist' in file.lower() and file.endswith('.json'): existing_files.append(file) print(f"Found previous analysis: {file}") # Load previous findings if available previous_names = [] if existing_files: for file in existing_files: try: with open(f'workspace/{file}', 'r') as f: data = json.load(f) # Extract any pianist names mentioned if 'unique_pianist_names' in data: previous_names.extend(data['unique_pianist_names']) elif 'potential_pianist_names' in data: previous_names.extend(data['potential_pianist_names']) except Exception as e: print(f"Could not load {file}: {str(e)}") # Remove duplicates and filter relevant names filtered_names = [] for name in set(previous_names): # Filter out obvious non-pianist names if not any(term in name.lower() for term in ['wikipedia', 'classical clips', 'grand piano', 'records', 'the pianist']): if len(name.split()) == 2: # Likely a real person name filtered_names.append(name) print(f"\nFiltered pianist names from previous searches: {len(filtered_names)}") for name in sorted(filtered_names): print(f" - {name}") # Define new targeted search queries targeted_queries = [ "\"25 year hiatus\" pianist classical music comeback", "pianist retirement 25 years return Faur√©", "\"first complete Faur√© piano works\" concert history", "Germaine Thyssens-Valentin complete Faur√© piano works", "Lucas Debargue Faur√© complete piano cycle", "Laurent Wagschal Faur√© piano complete recordings" ] # Add searches for specific names found previously for name in filtered_names[:3]: # Limit to top 3 to avoid too many searches targeted_queries.append(f'\"{name}\" 25 year hiatus pianist') targeted_queries.append(f'\"{name}\" Faur√© complete piano works') print(f"\n=== CONDUCTING {len(targeted_queries)} TARGETED SEARCHES ===\n") # Initialize searcher searcher = DDGS(timeout=10) # Store all results targeted_results = [] search_errors = [] for query_index, query in enumerate(targeted_queries, 1): print(f"--- Targeted Search {query_index}/{len(targeted_queries)}: {query} ---") try: results = searcher.text( query, max_results=3, # Fewer results per query since we have more queries page=1, backend=["duckduckgo"], safesearch="off", region="en-us" ) if results and len(results) > 0: print(f"Found {len(results)} results") for result_index, result in enumerate(results, 1): title = result.get('title', 'No title') snippet = result.get('body', result.get('snippet', 'No snippet')) url = result.get('href', result.get('url', 'No URL')) print(f" Result {result_index}: {title[:60]}...") # Store result targeted_result = { 'query': query, 'query_index': query_index, 'result_index': result_index, 'title': title, 'snippet': snippet, 'url': url } targeted_results.append(targeted_result) else: print("No results returned") except Exception as e: error_msg = f"Targeted search {query_index} failed: {str(e)}" print(error_msg) search_errors.append(error_msg) time.sleep(1.5) # Shorter delay since we have more searches print() print(f"=== TARGETED SEARCH COMPLETE ===\n") print(f"Total targeted results collected: {len(targeted_results)}") print(f"Search errors: {len(search_errors)}") # Save raw targeted results targeted_data = { 'objective': 'Find specific pianist with 25-year hiatus who first performed complete Faur√© piano works', 'search_type': 'targeted_follow_up', 'timestamp': '2024-12-19', 'total_queries': len(targeted_queries), 'successful_results': len(targeted_results), 'search_errors': search_errors, 'targeted_results': targeted_results } with open('workspace/pianist_faure_targeted_results.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(targeted_data, f, indent=2) print(f"Targeted results saved to: workspace/pianist_faure_targeted_results.json\n") # Process the targeted results immediately with simple operations print("=== PROCESSING TARGETED RESULTS ===\n") highly_relevant = [] specific_leads = [] all_names_found = [] for i, result in enumerate(targeted_results, 1): title = result['title'] snippet = result['snippet'] url = result['url'] query = result['query'] # Create combined text for analysis combined_text = f"{title} {snippet}".lower() print(f"--- Processing Targeted Result {i} ---") print(f"Title: {title}") print(f"Query: {query}") print(f"URL: {url}") print(f"Snippet: {snippet[:150]}..." if len(snippet) > 150 else f"Snippet: {snippet}") # Check for key indicators has_hiatus = any(term in combined_text for term in ['hiatus', 'retirement', 'comeback', 'return', 'break', 'absence']) has_25_years = '25' in combined_text and 'year' in combined_text has_faure = any(term in combined_text for term in ['faur√©', 'faure', 'gabriel']) has_complete = any(term in combined_text for term in ['complete', 'entire', 'all', 'full', 'cycle']) has_first = 'first' in combined_text has_pianist = any(term in combined_text for term in ['pianist', 'piano', 'performer']) # Calculate specificity score specificity_score = sum([has_hiatus, has_25_years, has_faure, has_complete, has_first, has_pianist]) # Show analysis factors = [] if has_hiatus: factors.append('Hiatus') if has_25_years: factors.append('25-Years') if has_faure: factors.append('Faur√©') if has_complete: factors.append('Complete') if has_first: factors.append('First') if has_pianist: factors.append('Pianist') print(f"Specificity Score: {specificity_score}/6 ({', '.join(factors) if factors else 'No key factors'})") # Extract names import re name_pattern = r'\b[A-Z][a-z]{2,}\s+[A-Z][a-z]{2,}\b' found_names = re.findall(name_pattern, f"{title} {snippet}") # Filter names exclude_terms = { 'Gabriel Faur√©', 'New York', 'Los Angeles', 'United States', 'Great Britain', 'Piano Music', 'Complete Works', 'Classical Music', 'Concert Hall', 'Classic FM', 'Sony Classical', 'Music Web', 'Piano World', 'Red Balloon', 'Century Rec', 'Higher Hz', 'Chamber Music', 'Lincoln Center', 'Bru Zane', 'Roman Polanski', 'Adrien Brody', 'Ronald Harwood', 'Victor Hugo', 'Apple Music', 'Amazon Music' } filtered_names = [name for name in found_names if name not in exclude_terms] if filtered_names: print(f"Names Found: {', '.join(filtered_names)}") all_names_found.extend(filtered_names) # Check for specific promising indicators if has_25_years and has_hiatus: print("*** HIGHLY PROMISING: Contains both 25-year and hiatus references ***") specific_leads.append({ 'title': title, 'snippet': snippet, 'url': url, 'query': query, 'reason': '25-year hiatus mentioned' }) if 'thyssens' in combined_text or 'valentin' in combined_text: print("*** SPECIFIC LEAD: Thyssens-Valentin mentioned ***") specific_leads.append({ 'title': title, 'snippet': snippet, 'url': url, 'query': query, 'reason': 'Thyssens-Valentin mentioned' }) if has_first and has_complete and has_faure: print("*** PROMISING: First complete Faur√© performance mentioned ***") # Add to highly relevant if score >= 4 if specificity_score >= 4: highly_relevant.append({ 'title': title, 'snippet': snippet, 'url': url, 'query': query, 'specificity_score': specificity_score, 'factors': factors, 'names_found': filtered_names }) print("‚úì Added to highly relevant results") print() # Remove duplicate names unique_names = list(set(all_names_found)) print(f"=== TARGETED SEARCH ANALYSIS SUMMARY ===\n") print(f"Total targeted results processed: {len(targeted_results)}") print(f"Highly relevant results (score >= 4): {len(highly_relevant)}") print(f"Specific leads identified: {len(specific_leads)}") print(f"Unique names found: {len(unique_names)}") if unique_names: print(f"\nNew pianist names discovered:") for name in sorted(unique_names): print(f" - {name}") if specific_leads: print(f"\n=== SPECIFIC LEADS TO INVESTIGATE ===\n") for i, lead in enumerate(specific_leads, 1): print(f"--- Lead {i}: {lead['reason']} ---") print(f"Title: {lead['title']}") print(f"URL: {lead['url']}") print(f"Query: {lead['query']}") print(f"Snippet: {lead['snippet'][:200]}..." if len(lead['snippet']) > 200 else f"Snippet: {lead['snippet']}") print() if highly_relevant: print(f"=== HIGHLY RELEVANT RESULTS ===\n") sorted_relevant = sorted(highly_relevant, key=lambda x: x['specificity_score'], reverse=True) for i, result in enumerate(sorted_relevant, 1): print(f"--- Highly Relevant {i} (Score: {result['specificity_score']}/6) ---") print(f"Title: {result['title']}") print(f"URL: {result['url']}") print(f"Factors: {', '.join(result['factors'])}") if result['names_found']: print(f"Names: {', '.join(result['names_found'])}") print(f"Snippet: {result['snippet'][:200]}..." if len(result['snippet']) > 200 else f"Snippet: {result['snippet']}") print() # Save comprehensive targeted analysis final_targeted_analysis = { 'objective': 'Find specific pianist with 25-year hiatus who first performed complete Faur√© piano works', 'search_phase': 'targeted_follow_up', 'analysis_completed': True, 'total_targeted_results': len(targeted_results), 'highly_relevant_count': len(highly_relevant), 'specific_leads_count': len(specific_leads), 'unique_names_found': unique_names, 'specific_leads': specific_leads, 'highly_relevant_results': sorted_relevant if highly_relevant else [], 'key_findings': [ f'Conducted {len(targeted_queries)} targeted searches', f'Found {len(specific_leads)} specific leads to investigate', f'Identified {len(unique_names)} new potential pianist names', f'Located {len(highly_relevant)} highly relevant sources' ], 'immediate_next_steps': [ 'Investigate any specific leads found', 'Research each unique pianist name individually', 'Focus on Thyssens-Valentin if mentioned in results', 'Check academic sources for Faur√© performance history', 'Search French language sources if needed' ] } with open('workspace/pianist_faure_targeted_analysis.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(final_targeted_analysis, f, indent=2) print(f"Targeted analysis saved to: workspace/pianist_faure_targeted_analysis.json") # Create final summary final_summary = { 'search_status': 'Targeted follow-up searches completed', 'total_searches_conducted': len(targeted_queries), 'key_discoveries': { 'specific_leads': len(specific_leads), 'highly_relevant_results': len(highly_relevant), 'new_pianist_names': unique_names }, 'most_promising_leads': [lead['title'] for lead in specific_leads[:3]], 'next_phase': 'Individual investigation of specific leads and names' } with open('workspace/pianist_search_final_summary.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(final_summary, f, indent=2) print(f"Final summary saved to: workspace/pianist_search_final_summary.json") print(f"\n=== TARGETED SEARCH INVESTIGATION COMPLETE ===\n") print("Successfully conducted targeted follow-up searches based on previous findings.") print(f"\nKey achievements:") print(f"‚úì Conducted {len(targeted_queries)} targeted searches") print(f"‚úì Found {len(specific_leads)} specific leads requiring investigation") print(f"‚úì Identified {len(highly_relevant)} highly relevant results") print(f"‚úì Discovered {len(unique_names)} new potential pianist names") print(f"‚úì Created comprehensive analysis for next phase of investigation") print(f"\nFiles created:") for file in os.listdir('workspace'): if 'targeted' in file.lower() or 'final' in file.lower(): if file.endswith('.json'): file_size = os.path.getsize(f'workspace/{file}') print(f" - {file} ({file_size:,} bytes)")

- Film historian verifying Thorsten Schuette‚Äôs participation in the Oberhausen Short Film Festival in July 1965 to document the director‚Äôs early career timeline

except Exception as e:
print(f"‚ùå Error during search {i}: {str(e)}")
failed_searches += 1
continue

import os import requests import json from datetime import datetime import time # Get SerpAPI key from environment variables api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY") if api_key is None: print("Error: Missing API key. Make sure you have SERPAPI_API_KEY in your environment variables.") print("Please set the environment variable and try again.") else: print("API key found, proceeding with classical music recording research...") print("Research objective: Identify Germaine Thyssens-Valentin's recording reissue entity") print("Secondary objective: Identify 1955 Bayreuth Wagner Ring Cycle reissue entity") print("Final objective: Compare entities and verify Thyssens-Valentin's profession") print("=" * 80) # Define comprehensive search queries for Germaine Thyssens-Valentin thyssens_queries = [ 'Germaine Thyssens-Valentin recordings discography', 'Germaine Thyssens-Valentin reissue record label', '"Germaine Thyssens-Valentin" recordings remastered', 'Germaine Thyssens-Valentin classical music recordings', 'Germaine Thyssens-Valentin singer opera recordings', 'Germaine Thyssens-Valentin CD reissue label', 'Germaine Thyssens-Valentin discography record company', 'Germaine Thyssens-Valentin historical recordings reissued' ] # Define search queries for 1955 Bayreuth Wagner Ring Cycle bayreuth_queries = [ '1955 Bayreuth Wagner Ring Cycle Joseph Keilberth Hans Hotter recording', 'Bayreuth 1955 Ring Cycle Keilberth Hotter reissue', '"Joseph Keilberth" "Hans Hotter" 1955 Bayreuth Ring recording', 'Bayreuth Festival 1955 Ring Cycle recording reissued', '1955 Bayreuth Ring des Nibelungen Keilberth recording label', 'Hans Hotter Wotan 1955 Bayreuth Ring Cycle CD reissue', 'Joseph Keilberth 1955 Bayreuth Wagner Ring recording company' ] # Combine all queries all_queries = thyssens_queries + bayreuth_queries print(f"Starting comprehensive research with {len(all_queries)} targeted queries...") print(f"Phase 1: Germaine Thyssens-Valentin research ({len(thyssens_queries)} queries)") print(f"Phase 2: 1955 Bayreuth Ring Cycle research ({len(bayreuth_queries)} queries)") print("=" * 80) # Store all search results for analysis all_results = [] successful_searches = 0 failed_searches = 0 current_phase = "" # Perform searches with different targeted queries for i, query in enumerate(all_queries, 1): # Determine current research phase if i <= len(thyssens_queries): if current_phase != "Thyssens-Valentin": current_phase = "Thyssens-Valentin" print(f"\n\nüéµ PHASE 1: GERMAINE THYSSENS-VALENTIN RESEARCH") print("=" * 50) else: if current_phase != "Bayreuth": current_phase = "Bayreuth" print(f"\n\nüé≠ PHASE 2: 1955 BAYREUTH RING CYCLE RESEARCH") print("=" * 50) print(f"\nSearch {i}/{len(all_queries)} [{current_phase}]: {query}") print("-" * 70) # Prepare API request parameters params = { "q": query, "api_key": api_key, "engine": "google", "google_domain": "google.com", "safe": "off", "num": 10, # Focused number for quality analysis "type": "search" } try: # Make API request to SerpAPI response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: results = response.json() if results.get("organic_results"): print(f"‚úÖ Found {len(results['organic_results'])} results for search {i}") successful_searches += 1 # Process and analyze results immediately for j, result in enumerate(results["organic_results"], 1): try: title = result.get('title', 'No title') link = result.get('link', 'No link') snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet') print(f"\nResult {j}:") print(f"Title: {title}") print(f"Link: {link}") print(f"Snippet: {snippet[:200]}...") # Truncated for readability # Immediate analysis to identify key information title_lower = title.lower() if title else '' snippet_lower = snippet.lower() if snippet else '' combined_content = f"{title_lower} {snippet_lower}" # Define search indicators for each phase if current_phase == "Thyssens-Valentin": key_indicators = [ 'germaine thyssens-valentin', 'thyssens-valentin', 'germaine thyssens', 'recording', 'recordings', 'discography', 'reissue', 'reissued', 'record label', 'cd', 'album', 'classical', 'opera', 'singer', 'soprano', 'mezzo-soprano', 'vocal', 'voice' ] record_labels = [ 'emi', 'decca', 'deutsche grammophon', 'philips', 'columbia', 'rca', 'warner', 'sony', 'universal', 'naxos', 'melodiya', 'testament', 'pristine', 'guild', 'biddulph', 'pearl' ] else: # Bayreuth phase key_indicators = [ 'bayreuth', 'wagner', 'ring cycle', 'ring des nibelungen', 'joseph keilberth', 'keilberth', 'hans hotter', 'hotter', 'wotan', '1955', 'recording', 'reissue', 'cd' ] record_labels = [ 'emi', 'decca', 'deutsche grammophon', 'philips', 'columbia', 'rca', 'warner', 'sony', 'universal', 'melodiya', 'testament', 'pristine', 'guild', 'biddulph', 'pearl', 'orfeo', 'gala' ] # Count matches indicator_matches = [ind for ind in key_indicators if ind in combined_content] label_matches = [label for label in record_labels if label in combined_content] total_relevance = len(indicator_matches) + len(label_matches) * 2 # Weight label matches higher # Immediate relevance assessment if indicator_matches: print(f"üéØ KEY INDICATORS: {indicator_matches}") if label_matches: print(f"üè∑Ô∏è RECORD LABELS: {label_matches}") if total_relevance >= 3: print(f"‚≠ê HIGH RELEVANCE SCORE: {total_relevance}") elif total_relevance >= 1: print(f"‚úì Potentially relevant: {total_relevance}") # Store result with immediate analysis all_results.append({ 'search_number': i, 'research_phase': current_phase, 'query_text': query, 'result_number': j, 'title': title, 'link': link, 'snippet': snippet, 'indicator_matches': indicator_matches, 'label_matches': label_matches, 'total_relevance': total_relevance, 'analysis_timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat() }) print("-" * 40) except Exception as result_error: print(f"‚ùå Error processing result {j}: {str(result_error)}") continue else: print(f"‚ùå No organic results found for search {i}: '{query}'") failed_searches += 1 else: print(f"‚ùå Error: API request failed with status {response.status_code}") failed_searches += 1 except Exception as e: print(f"‚ùå Error during search {i}: {str(e)}") failed_searches += 1 continue # Small delay between requests time.sleep(1) print("\n" + "=" * 80) # Create workspace directory if needed if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # Save results with timestamp timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S") results_file = f"workspace/recording_reissue_research_results_{timestamp}.json" search_data = { 'search_timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat(), 'research_objective': 'Identify recording reissue entities for Germaine Thyssens-Valentin and 1955 Bayreuth Ring Cycle', 'search_strategy': 'Two-phase approach: artist discography research + specific recording research', 'total_queries': len(all_queries), 'thyssens_queries': len(thyssens_queries), 'bayreuth_queries': len(bayreuth_queries), 'successful_searches': successful_searches, 'failed_searches': failed_searches, 'total_results': len(all_results), 'queries_executed': all_queries, 'results': all_results } with open(results_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(search_data, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f"\n\nüìä COMPREHENSIVE RESEARCH SUMMARY:") print(f"Total research queries executed: {len(all_queries)}") print(f"Successful searches: {successful_searches}") print(f"Failed searches: {failed_searches}") print(f"Total results collected: {len(all_results)}") print(f"Results saved to: {results_file}") # Immediate analysis of collected results print("\n\nüîç IMMEDIATE ANALYSIS OF RESEARCH RESULTS:") print("=" * 55) # Categorize results by research phase and relevance thyssens_results = [r for r in all_results if r['research_phase'] == 'Thyssens-Valentin'] bayreuth_results = [r for r in all_results if r['research_phase'] == 'Bayreuth'] high_relevance_thyssens = [r for r in thyssens_results if r['total_relevance'] >= 3] high_relevance_bayreuth = [r for r in bayreuth_results if r['total_relevance'] >= 3] # Extract record label mentions thyssens_labels = set() bayreuth_labels = set() for result in thyssens_results: thyssens_labels.update(result['label_matches']) for result in bayreuth_results: bayreuth_labels.update(result['label_matches']) print(f"\nüìã RESEARCH PHASE BREAKDOWN:") print(f"Thyssens-Valentin results: {len(thyssens_results)}") print(f"Bayreuth Ring Cycle results: {len(bayreuth_results)}") print(f"High relevance Thyssens-Valentin: {len(high_relevance_thyssens)}") print(f"High relevance Bayreuth: {len(high_relevance_bayreuth)}") print(f"\nüè∑Ô∏è RECORD LABELS IDENTIFIED:") print(f"Thyssens-Valentin associated labels: {sorted(list(thyssens_labels)) if thyssens_labels else 'None found'}") print(f"Bayreuth Ring Cycle associated labels: {sorted(list(bayreuth_labels)) if bayreuth_labels else 'None found'}") # Check for common labels common_labels = thyssens_labels.intersection(bayreuth_labels) if common_labels: print(f"\nüéØ COMMON LABELS FOUND: {sorted(list(common_labels))}") print(f"These labels appear in both research phases - potential matches!") else: print(f"\n‚ö†Ô∏è No common labels found between the two research subjects") # Display most promising findings if high_relevance_thyssens: print("\n\nüéµ HIGH RELEVANCE THYSSENS-VALENTIN FINDINGS:") print("=" * 45) for i, result in enumerate(high_relevance_thyssens[:3], 1): # Top 3 print(f"\n{i}. {result['title']}") print(f" Query: {result['query_text']}") print(f" Link: {result['link']}") print(f" Snippet: {result['snippet'][:150]}...") print(f" Relevance Score: {result['total_relevance']}") print(f" Key indicators: {result['indicator_matches']}") print(f" Record labels: {result['label_matches']}") print("-" * 40) if high_relevance_bayreuth: print("\n\nüé≠ HIGH RELEVANCE BAYREUTH RING CYCLE FINDINGS:") print("=" * 45) for i, result in enumerate(high_relevance_bayreuth[:3], 1): # Top 3 print(f"\n{i}. {result['title']}") print(f" Query: {result['query_text']}") print(f" Link: {result['link']}") print(f" Snippet: {result['snippet'][:150]}...") print(f" Relevance Score: {result['total_relevance']}") print(f" Key indicators: {result['indicator_matches']}") print(f" Record labels: {result['label_matches']}") print("-" * 40) #
